n \in \mathbb{N}
\Phi_n \in \mathbb C[x]
n
\Phi_2 =(x+1)
\Phi_4 = (x-i)(x+i) = x^2+1
k|n
0<k<n
\Phi_n | \frac {x^n-1}{x^k-1} 
z_0 \in \Bbb C
n^{th}
z_0^n=1
z_0^k \neq 1 
k<n
P(x)=\frac{x^n-1}{x^k-1}
P(z_0)=\frac{z_0^n-1}{z_0^k-1}=0
P(x)=\frac{x^n-1}{x^k-1}=x^{k(l-1)}+x^{k(l-2)}+x^{k(l-3)}+....+1
P
\Phi | P
